# Chrome Extension: Link Saver

Lead tracker is a Chrome extension that helps users save links and manage them conveniently within the browser. With this extension, users can save the URLs of their current tabs, delete saved links, and even delete all saved URLs with ease.

## Features

- **Save Current Tab URL:** Save the URL of the current tab with just one click.
- **Save Links:** Save any URL manually by entering it into the extension.
- **Delete Feature:** Easily delete individual saved URLs or delete all saved URLs at once using the "Delete All" button.

## Tech Stack

- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript

## Installation

To use the Link Saver Chrome extension, follow these steps:

1. Clone or download this repository to your local machine.
2. Open Google Chrome.
3. Navigate to Manage chrome extension `chrome://extensions/`.
4. Click on "Load unpacked" and select the directory where you cloned/downloaded the extension.
5. The Link Saver extension should now be installed and ready to use.

## Usage

1. After installing the extension, you'll see its icon in the Chrome toolbar.
2. Click on the icon to open the Link Saver popup.
3. To save the URL of the current tab, simply click on the "Save" button.
4. To manually save a URL, enter it into the input field and click on "Save".
5. To delete a saved URL, click on the "Delete" button next to it.
6. To delete all saved URLs, click on the "Delete All" button.

